Share with:
Chief Executive Officer Job (CEO Job) (Joint-Venture), Jakarta, Indonesia
Country:
Indonesia
Function:
Operations
Industry:
Banking & Finance
Position type:
Permanent
Salary:
Negotiable
Created:
05 May 2014
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of an expanding joint-venture E-commerce company within the financial services industry, in Indonesia. Our respected client is seeking a candidate for the job of Chief Executive Officer (CEO), to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia. The winning candidate will be required to develop models, leverage social media platforms to drive customer engagement and implement ways to achieve profit growth for this start-up e-commerce firm. The successful applicant must be a great communicator and leader who drives enthusiasm, momentum and collaboration around a shared vision for sustainable businesses. The winning candidate will report directly to the respective partners of the joint-ventures.
Key job responsibilities include:
Plans, directs, organizes and schedules the strategies and activities of the firm.
Oversee the company’s’ online sales and brand presence.
Conveying a consistent brand image that attracts customers by enticing sales on the web.
Analyse the business and operations of the start-up and online marketing in Indonesia.
Optimize the e-commerce platform by establishing best proven practices, processes, measurement and forecasting systems.
Plan and execute the strategic move of the start-up and liaise with the partners.
Lead and execute a methodology that accurately predicts sales, orders, customer acquisition and costs for all programs.
Support company and department goals and achieve business unit KPI's.
Liaise with peers in Finance, Customer Support, IT, and Creative to deliver an unrivalled customer experience for all sales channels.
Provide backend analysis and recommendations after testing to continuously improve the customer experience and grow sales and contribution.
Analyse and provide reporting on program KPI's – identifying opportunities for growth and improving efficiency.
Execute trend analysis, monitoring and competitive benchmarking.
Requirements:
Bachelor’s degree in IT or business major from a reputable university
At least 5 years of senior managerial experience
Strong knowledge in technology and the digital space; will be an advantage if has deep exposure in Online & E-commerce, marketing experience is a strong plus
Strong drive for continuous improvement – maximizing growth, accelerating the rate of new customer acquisition and improving program profitability
Demonstrate a an entrepreneurial attitude
An analytical, problem solving and results-driven approach to e-commerce challenges and opportunities
Ability to work well under pressure and balance multiple priorities
Combination of technical, infrastructure, and most importantly business minded to improve the company
Must be willing to work in a fast-paced environment with an openness to change as our company grows.
Strong communication and negotiation skills
Effective management of programs and/or services within area assigned
Ability to understand the needs of customers
Strong written and presentation skills
Good leadership skills
Enthusiasm for the business you work in
Prociency in English will be an advantage
All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence.